<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Library App</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;700&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body class="site-shell">
    <header class="top-nav wrap">
        <a class="brand" href="/">ShelfPilot</a>
        <nav class="nav-links">
            <a href="/books">Books</a>
            <a href="/books/new">Add Book</a>
            <a href="/register">Register</a>
            <a href="/login">Login</a>
            <a id="profile-link" href="/profile" hidden>Profile</a>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="wrap">
        <section class="hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Built for focused readers</p>
            <h1>Keep your reading list sharp and searchable.</h1>
            <p class="hero-copy">Track books, mark progress, and keep your collection clean without spreadsheet chaos.</p>
            <div class="cta-row">
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/books">Browse Library</a>
                <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/books/new">Add New Book</a>
            </div>
            <div class="stats-card">
                <p><span>Total books:</span> live from your database</p>
                <p><span>Status:</span> completed or in progress</p>
                <p><span>Flow:</span> add, edit, ship reading habits</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="proof-grid">
            <article>
                <h2>Simple by design</h2>
                <p>No bloat. Just the screens you need to manage your reading list fast.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Honest workflow</h2>
                <p>Add a title, update progress, and move on to your next book.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h2>Open stack</h2>
                <p>Express + MongoDB powering a straightforward, hackable project.</p>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section class="steps">
            <h2>Your 3-step reading flow</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Add a book in seconds</li>
                <li>Update status while you read</li>
                <li>Review your collection anytime</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </main>

    <script>
        const profileLink = document.getElementById('profile-link');
        const token = localStorage.getItem('authToken');

        if (profileLink && token) {
            profileLink.hidden = false;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>